---
import MainLayout from '../../../layouts/docs-layout.astro';
const flowExample = `User runs CLI command
         ↓
System checks: Is this feature AI-powered?
         ↓
If YES:
  - Check user's MCU balance
  - If balance greater than 0: Execute task, deduct 1 MCU
  - If balance equals 0: Show insufficient credits message
         ↓
If NO:
  - Execute freely (no cost)`;

const pricingTiers = `// Pricing tiers (NOWPayments)
Starter: $49/mo → 200 MCU credits
  - Good for: Side projects, hobby CLI usage

Pro: $149/mo → 1,000 MCU credits
  - Good for: Teams, production tools

Enterprise: $499/mo → Unlimited MCU credits
  - Good for: Large teams, commercial use`;

const stripePacks = `// Stripe credit packs
10 MCU credits: $5 (50 cents per MCU)
50 MCU credits: $20 (40 cents per MCU)
100 MCU credits: $35 (35 cents per MCU)`;
---
<MainLayout title="Open Source Monetization: Credit-Based Billing for CLI Tools" description="How to monetize an open-source CLI tool using MCU credits, Polar subscriptions, Stripe, and license keys. Architecture patterns + code examples.">
  <article class="blog-post" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem">
    <h1 class="gradient-text">Open Source Monetization: Credit-Based Billing for CLI Tools</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);margin-bottom:2rem">Published March 21, 2026 · 9 min read</p>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Open Source Monetization Problem</h2>
      <p>You've built a beloved open-source CLI tool. Thousands of stars on GitHub. Active community. But you're not making money.</p>
      <p>Traditional options are terrible:</p>
      <ul style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);line-height:1.8">
        <li><strong>Patreon/Open Collective:</strong> Gets you $500-2K/month if you're lucky. Doesn't scale.</li>
        <li><strong>SaaS conversion:</strong> Removes the open-source advantage. Users abandon you for free forks.</li>
        <li><strong>Sponsorships:</strong> Feels like selling out. Requires constant pitching.</li>
        <li><strong>Support contracts:</strong> High friction. Only works if you have enterprise users.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>The solution?</strong> Credit-based billing. Keep your CLI open-source and free, but charge for AI-powered features or high-volume usage.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The MCU Credit Model</h2>
      <p><strong>MCU = Mission Completion Unit.</strong> One credit equals one meaningful task completion (writing, coding, analysis).</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">How It Works</h3>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{flowExample}</code></pre>

      <p>Examples of free vs. paid:</p>
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1rem 0">
        <tr style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container)">
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Feature</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Cost</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Why</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)"><code>mekong list</code> - List files</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Free</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Local filesystem operation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)"><code>mekong cook</code> - AI mission</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">1-5 MCU</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">LLM inference costs money</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)"><code>mekong fix</code> - Debug issue</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">2-3 MCU</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Requires analysis + generation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)"><code>mekong deploy</code> - Deploy code</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Free</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Just orchestrates your infrastructure</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)"><code>mekong review</code> - Code review</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">3 MCU</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Analysis-heavy, requires LLM</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>Key insight:</strong> Users don't pay for the CLI. They pay for the AI computations it enables.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>Monetization Architecture (4 Revenue Streams)</h2>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">Stream 1: MCU Credit Subscriptions (Recurring)</h3>
      <p>Users subscribe to monthly credit allowances via NOWPayments webhooks.</p>

      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{pricingTiers}</code></pre>

      <p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> 80% of revenue (assuming 200 users on Pro at $149/mo = $29,800 MRR)</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">Stream 2: Pay-As-You-Go (Variable)</h3>
      <p>Users without subscriptions can buy credits à la carte via Stripe.</p>

      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{stripePacks}</code></pre>

      <p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> 10% of revenue (impulse buyers, infrequent usage)</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">Stream 3: Seat Licenses (Enterprise)</h3>
      <p>Team of 5+ users? Sell per-seat annual licenses for commercial use.</p>

      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{`// Annual licenses (via NOWPayments)
Team License: $299/year per seat
  - 5 seats = $1,495/year
  - Features: Shared credit pool, team management

Business License: $699/year per seat
  - For companies over 100 employees
  - Features: All Team + dedicated support`}</code></pre>

      <p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> 10% of revenue (converts 5-10% of user base to team licenses)</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">Stream 4: API Tier (Programmatic Access)</h3>
      <p>Developers building on top of your CLI pay per API call.</p>

      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{`// HTTP API (for embedding Mekong in other tools)
POST https://api.agencyos.network/v1/missions
Authorization: Bearer sk_live_...
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "command": "mekong cook 'write marketing email'",
  "user_id": "user_123"
}

// API pricing (pay-as-you-go only)
$0.50 per API call (1 MCU equivalent)
No free tier, starts with $50 prepaid credits`}</code></pre>

      <p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> Negligible initially, but upside as ecosystem grows</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>Financial Projections</h2>

      <p><strong>Assumptions:</strong> 1,000 total users at steady state</p>

      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1rem 0">
        <tr style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container)">
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Segment</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Users</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">MRR/User</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Total MRR</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Free tier (10 MCU)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">700</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Pay-as-you-go (occasional)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">150</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$5</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$750</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Starter ($49)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">80</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$49</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$3,920</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Pro ($149)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">50</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$149</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$7,450</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Enterprise ($499)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">20</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$499</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$9,980</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);font-weight:bold">
          <td colspan="3" style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">TOTAL MRR</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$22,100</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>At 1,000 users:</strong> $22,100 MRR = $265K ARR (before payment processor fees)</p>

      <p><strong>Path to $1M ARR:</strong></p>
      <ul style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);line-height:1.8">
        <li>Reach 4,500 users (10x growth)</li>
        <li>Convert 10% to paid (instead of 2% currently)</li>
        <li>Increase average LTV through upsells</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>Key Learnings</h2>

      <ul style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);line-height:1.8">
        <li><strong>Free tier is essential:</strong> 70% of users will try free. Remove friction.</li>
        <li><strong>Freemium works:</strong> Credit model converts 2-5% of free users to paid. That's your TAM.</li>
        <li><strong>Subscription wins:</strong> $149/mo users generate 30x more ARR than $5 one-time buyers.</li>
        <li><strong>NOWPayments is simple:</strong> Webhooks handle subscriptions automatically. No billing infrastructure needed.</li>
        <li><strong>HTTP 402 is underused:</strong> Most apps ignore it. Use it clearly for payment-required errors.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparency wins:</strong> Show cost before execution. Users will upgrade if the value is clear.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>How to Start</h2>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">1. Add credit tracking to your database</h3>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{`CREATE TABLE users (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT UNIQUE,
  mcu_balance INT DEFAULT 10,
  subscription_tier TEXT,
  created_at DATETIME
);

CREATE TABLE transactions (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id TEXT,
  action TEXT,
  amount_mcu INT,
  source TEXT,
  timestamp DATETIME
);`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">2. Add middleware for credit checking</h3>
      <p>Implement a middleware that checks user balance before executing paid features.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">3. Set up NOWPayments webhooks</h3>
      <p>Listen for subscription.created, subscription.updated, and subscription.cancelled events.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">4. Update your CLI</h3>
      <p>Show balance before execution. Return HTTP 402 when credits run out.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">5. Launch</h3>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{`mekong deploy --platform cloudflare
# Your API is live on workers.dev

# Update CLI to point to your API
export LLM_API_BASE=https://your-api.cloudflare.dev

# Announce the feature
# "Now monetized! Free tier for everyone."`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <div style="margin-top:3rem;padding:2rem;background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);border-radius:12px;text-align:center">
      <h3>Fork & Deploy Your Own</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant)">The full Mekong RaaS billing architecture is open-source. Deploy in 30 minutes.</p>
      <md-elevated-button onclick="location.href='https://github.com/openclaw/mekong-cli'">View on GitHub</md-elevated-button>
    </div>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

